fastPathPortSecurity.name: fastPathPortSecurity
fastPathPortSecurity.description: The Ubiquiti Private MIB for EdgeSwitch Port Security Feature.

agentGlobalPortSecurityMode.name: agentGlobalPortSecurityMode
agentGlobalPortSecurityMode.description: Mode showing whether at the global level, port security is enabled or not.

agentPortSecurityTable.name: agentPortSecurityTable
agentPortSecurityTable.description: A table for Port Security and associated functionality.

agentPortSecurityEntry.name: agentPortSecurityEntry
agentPortSecurityEntry.description: Represents entry for port security table

agentPortSecurityMode.name: agentPortSecurityMode
agentPortSecurityMode.description: Mode showing whether at port level security is enabled or not.

agentPortSecurityDynamicLimit.name: agentPortSecurityDynamicLimit
agentPortSecurityDynamicLimit.description: This variable signifies the limit of dynamically locked MAC addresses allowed on a specific port.

agentPortSecurityStaticLimit.name: agentPortSecurityStaticLimit
agentPortSecurityStaticLimit.description: This variable signifies the limit of statically locked MAC addresses allowed on a specific port.

agentPortSecurityViolationTrapMode.name: agentPortSecurityViolationTrapMode
agentPortSecurityViolationTrapMode.description: This variable is used to enable or disable the sending of new violation traps designating when a packet with a disallowed MAC address is received on a locked port.

agentPortSecurityStaticMACs.name: agentPortSecurityStaticMACs
agentPortSecurityStaticMACs.description: This variable displays the statically locked MAC addresses for port. The list displayed in a particular fashion : 2 a0:b1:c2:d1:e3:a1,11 a0:b1:c2:d3:e4:f5 (i.e., VLAN MAC pairs followed by a 1 or 0 to indicate a sticky entry, separated by commas).

agentPortSecurityLastDiscardedMAC.name: agentPortSecurityLastDiscardedMAC
agentPortSecurityLastDiscardedMAC.description: This variable displays the vlan-id and source MAC address of the last packet that was discarded on a locked port.

agentPortSecurityMACAddressAdd.name: agentPortSecurityMACAddressAdd
agentPortSecurityMACAddressAdd.description: This MIB variable accepts a VLAN id, MAC address and the sticky value to be added to the list of statically locked MAC addresses on a port. The VLAN id, MAC address and sticky value combination would be entered in a particular fashion like :- 2 a0:b0:c0:d1:e2:a1 1(the vlan-id, MAC address and sticky value separated by blank-spaces).

agentPortSecurityMACAddressRemove.name: agentPortSecurityMACAddressRemove
agentPortSecurityMACAddressRemove.description: This MIB variable accepts a VLAN id and MAC address to be removed from the list of statically locked MAC addresses on a port.. The VLAN id and MAC address combination would be entered in a particular fashion like :- 2 a0:b0:c0:d1:e2:a1(the vlan-id and MAC address separated by a blank-space).

agentPortSecurityMACAddressMove.name: agentPortSecurityMACAddressMove
agentPortSecurityMACAddressMove.description: When this object is enabled, all the dynamically locked MAC addresses will be moved to statically locked addresses on a port. GET operation on this object will display disable.

agentPortSecurityStickyMode.name: agentPortSecurityStickyMode
agentPortSecurityStickyMode.description: This object is used to configure port level security sticky mode in a port.

agentPortSecurityDynamicTable.name: agentPortSecurityDynamicTable
agentPortSecurityDynamicTable.description: A table for Port Security Dynamic and associated functionality.

agentPortSecurityDynamicEntry.name: agentPortSecurityDynamicEntry
agentPortSecurityDynamicEntry.description: Represents entry for port MAC Locking table

agentPortSecurityDynamicVLANId.name: agentPortSecurityDynamicVLANId
agentPortSecurityDynamicVLANId.description: Source VLAN id of the packet that is received on the dynamically locked port.

agentPortSecurityDynamicMACAddress.name: agentPortSecurityDynamicMACAddress
agentPortSecurityDynamicMACAddress.description: Source MAC address of the packet that is received on the dynamically locked port.

agentGlobalPortSecurityStickyMode.name: agentGlobalPortSecurityStickyMode
agentGlobalPortSecurityStickyMode.description: This object is used to apply the Sticky Mode to all ports. This is write-only value. It always returns 'disable' on request

agentGlobalPortSecurityViolationTrapMode.name: agentGlobalPortSecurityViolationTrapMode
agentGlobalPortSecurityViolationTrapMode.description: This variable is used to enable or disable the sending of new violation traps designating when a packet with a disallowed MAC address is received on a locked port. The configuration will be done on all ports. This is write-only value. It always returns 'disable' on request

agentPortSecurityViolation.name: agentPortSecurityViolation
agentPortSecurityViolation.description: Sent when a packet is received on a locked port with a source MAC address that is not allowed.
